# Gitleaks false positive suppressions
#
# Format: one fingerprint per line (SHA256 of the finding).
# These are pre-existing findings in the repo history that GitGuardian
# has confirmed as false positives. Suppressing here prevents gitleaks
# from failing CI on every PR due to historical commits.
#
# To find a fingerprint: run `gitleaks detect --report-format json`
# and copy the "Fingerprint" field from the finding.
